 of land, cultural heritage, and global ecology, Yahgulanaas disrupts the expected, allowing different ways of experiencing, knowing, and seeing the world to emerge.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArt, CanadianzBritish Columbiay21st century. 0aArt, Moderny21st century. 0aHaida artzBritish Columbiay21st century. 0aHaida artistszBritish Columbia. 0aNarrative art. 7aART / Native American.2bisacsh1 aKishigami, Nobuhiro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYahgulanaas, Michael Nicoll, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311141764640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486737540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774867375423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774867375/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-141764-6  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles